UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1053
1 (4) The department shall arrange for an annual conference of the property valuation
2 administrators, or the county officers whose duty it is to assess property for
3 taxation, to give them systematic instruction in the fair and just valuation and
4 assessment of property, and their duty in connection therewith. The conference
5 shall continue not more than five (5) days. The officers shall attend and take part in
6 the conference, unless prevented by illness or other reason satisfactory to the
7 commissioner. Any officer willfully failing to attend the conference may be
8 removed from office by the Circuit Court of the county where he was elected. If the
9 officer participates in all sessions of the conference, one-half (1/2) of his actual and
10 necessary expenses in attending the conference shall be paid by the state, and the
11 other half shall be paid by the county from which he attends. Each officer shall
12 prepare an itemized statement showing his actual and necessary expenses, and if it
13 is found regular and supported by proper receipts it shall be approved by the
14 department before payment.
